├── matric.html

├── intermediate.html

├── Teachers.html

├── campus Life 

├── About Us

├── Admission 

├── Career

│

└── README.md   (optional – project overview)

Purpose:

* Enhance UI/UX
* Visual representation of academy staff and environment

---

## 4. Main HTML Files

All pages are created using **HTML5** and styled using **Tailwind CSS**.

---

### 4.1 `index.html` (Home Page)

```
study zone/index.html
```

Description:

* Landing page of Study Zone Academy
* Introduces the academy
* Displays hero section, overview, and navigation

Main Sections:

* Header & Navigation Bar
* Hero Section
* About Summary
* Courses Overview
* Footer

---

### 4.2 `program.html` (Programs Page)

```
study zone/program.html
```

Description:

* Displays all academic programs offered
* Organized program-wise for clarity

Content Includes:

* Program cards
* Class categories
* Academic structure

---

### 4.3 `matric.html` (Matric Classes Page)

```
study zone/matric.html
```

Description:

* Dedicated page for Matric level education
* Shows subjects and class details

Purpose:

* Guide students for Matric admissions

---

### 4.4 `intermediate.html` (Intermediate Classes Page)

```
study zone/intermediate.html
```

Description:

* Intermediate (FSc / FA) related information
* Subject streams and preparation details

---

### 4.5 `Teachers.html` (Faculty Page)

```
study zone/Teachers.html
```

Description:

* Displays teaching staff
* Includes teacher images and names

Purpose:

* Build trust and credibility

---

## 5. Technologies Used (As per Project)

### Languages

* HTML5
* CSS3

### Framework

* Tailwind CSS

### Fonts

* Poppins – body text
* Sora – headings & buttons

### Tools

* VS Code
* Git & GitHub
* Browser Developer Tools

---

## 6. Design & Development Process

### Step 1: Folder Structure Setup

* Created root folder
* Organized images separately

### Step 2: Page Development

* Each academic level has its own HTML page
* Reusable navigation structure

### Step 3: Styling

* Utility-first approach using Tailwind CSS
* Responsive layout using Flexbox & Grid

### Step 4: Testing

* Responsive testing
* Cross-browser checks

---

## 7. Navigation Flow Diagram

```
User
 ↓
Home (index.html)
 ↓
Programs (program.html)
 ↓            ↓
Matric     Intermediate
 ↓
Teachers
```

---

## 8. Limitations

* Static website
* No backend
* No form submission logic

---

## 9. Future Enhancements

* Add JavaScript functionality
* Online admission form
* Backend integration
* Student portal

